    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, org.sbml.jsbml.util.TreeNodeWithChangeSupport, MEConstants

    public class MEReactionPlugin
extends MEAbstractXMLNodePlugin
implements MEConstants
    Implements attributes and methods to encode all information of reactions in a COBRAme model in SBML.

    Besides SBML core the packages fbc and groups are used in all reaction creating methods of this class. The groups package is used to encode the reaction type. The fbc package is used to encode the upper and lower bounds and the objective coefficient of the reaction.

    Author:
    Marc A. Voigt

      • addCOBRAmeSpeciesToReaction

        public void addCOBRAmeSpeciesToReaction(org.sbml.jsbml.Model model,
                                        org.sbml.jsbml.Reaction reaction,
                                        java.lang.String speciesId,
                                        java.lang.String coefficient)
                                 throws org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException
        Adds a single species from a COBRAme reaction list to the corresponding SBML reaction.

        In COBRAme reactions only possess one list for both reactants and products. When species are added from this list reactants and products need to be separated, the method does this by checking if the species' coefficient is negative. In COBRAme coefficients can also be complex formulas that depend on parameters. When such a coefficient is added the formula is checked for currently unknown parameters that need to be added to the ListOfParameters of the model. The check whether a species is a product or reactant is based on the first character in the string that is not an opening bracket, if this is a minus the species is assumed to be a reactant.

        Parameters:
        model - the SBML model
        reaction - the SBML reaction that the species should be added to
        speciesId - the id of the species
        coefficient - the coefficient of the species
        Throws:
        org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException

      • setBounds

        public void setBounds(org.sbml.jsbml.Model model,
                      org.sbml.jsbml.ext.fbc.FBCReactionPlugin fbcTempReaction,
                      java.lang.String upperBound,
                      java.lang.String lowerBound)
               throws org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException
        Sets the Bounds of a fbc reaction to a valid parameter. If there is no valid parameter a new one is created.

        In order to not create several parameters with the same value this method translates the value into a String that can be used as a valid SBML id. The method then searches the ListOfParameter for a parameter with the translated id. If no such parameter is found a new parameter is created.

        Parameters:
        model - the SBML model
        fbcTempReaction - the fbc plugin for the reaction
        upperBound - the designated upper bound
        lowerBound - the designated lower bound
        Throws:
        org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException

      • createSummaryVariableReaction

        public void createSummaryVariableReaction(org.sbml.jsbml.Model model,
                                          org.sbml.jsbml.ext.groups.GroupsModelPlugin groups,
                                          org.sbml.jsbml.ext.fbc.Objective objective,
                                          java.lang.String id,
                                          java.lang.String name,
                                          java.lang.String upperBound,
                                          java.lang.String lowerBound,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.String> speciesIds,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.String> coefficients,
                                          double objectiveCoefficient,
                                          java.lang.String variableKind)
                                   throws org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException
        Create and add a SummaryVariable Reaction to the model.

        In COBRAme this reaction type is used to apply global constraints to the model. This method adds the SBMLme exclusive attribute "variableKind" to the annotation of the reaction.

        Parameters:
        model - the SBML model
        groups - the GroupsModelPlugin of the SBML model
        objective - the active objective of the SBML model
        id - the id of the reaction to be added
        name - the name of the reaction, can be null
        upperBound - the upper bound of the reaction
        lowerBound - the lower bound of the reaction
        speciesIds - the list with the ids of all species in the reaction
        coefficients - the list with all species coefficients in the reaction, must have the same order as the list with species ids
        objectiveCoefficient - the coefficient of the flux objective of the reaction
        variableKind - can be either "continuous" or "discrete"
        Throws:
        org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException

      • createTranscriptionReaction

        public void createTranscriptionReaction(org.sbml.jsbml.Model model,
                                        org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLDocument sbol,
                                        org.sbml.jsbml.ext.groups.GroupsModelPlugin groups,
                                        org.sbml.jsbml.ext.fbc.Objective objective,
                                        java.lang.String id,
                                        java.lang.String name,
                                        java.lang.String dataId,
                                        double upperBound,

                                        java.util.List<java.lang.String> speciesIds,
                                        java.util.List<java.lang.String> coefficients,
                                        double objectiveCoefficient,
                                        java.lang.String variableKind,
                                        java.lang.String sequence,
                                        java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Double> subreactionMap)
                                 throws org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException,
                                        org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLValidationException
        Create and add a transcription reaction to the model.

        This method also creates a new ComponentDefinition with the given sequence in the SBOL document for the transcription unit. The method adds four SBMLme attributes to the annotation of the reaction, "variableKind", "dataId", "sequence" and "listOfSubreactionReferences". The attribute "sequence" contains the URI of the ComponentDefinition in the SBOL document for the transcription unit. The "listOfSubreactionReferences" contains all subreactions that take part in the reaction.

        Parameters:
        model - the SBML model
        sbol - the SBOL document to which the sequence should be added
        groups - the GroupsModelPlugin of the SBML model
        objective - the active objective of the SBML model
        id - the id of the reaction to be added
        name - the name of the reaction, can be null
        dataId - the id of the process data object that is referred by the reaction in COBRAme, cannot be null or empty string
        upperBound - the upper bound of the reaction
        lowerBound - the lower bound of the reaction
        speciesIds - the list with the ids of all species in the reaction
        coefficients - the list with all species coefficients in the reaction, must have the same order as the list with species ids
        objectiveCoefficient - the coefficient of the flux objective of the reaction
        variableKind - can be either "continuous" or "discrete"
        sequence - the nucleotide sequence of the transcription unit, cannot be null or empty string
        subreactionMap - the map with the ids and coefficients of the subreactions that take part in the reaction, may be null
        Throws:
        org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException
        org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLValidationException

                                       java.lang.String aminoAcid)
                                throws org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException,
                                       org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLValidationException
        Create and add a tRNA charging reaction to the model.

        The method adds the attributes "dataId", "keff", "variableKind", "synthetase", "codon", "aminoAcid" and "listOfSubreactionReferences" to the annotation of the reaction. The "listOfSubreactionReferences" contains all subreactions that take part in the reaction.

        Parameters:
        model - the SBML model
        groups - the GroupsModelPlugin of the SBML model
        objective - the active objective of the SBML model
        id - the id of the reaction to be added
        name - the name of the reaction, can be null
        dataId - the id of the process data object that is referred by the reaction in COBRAme, cannot be null or empty string
        upperBound - the upper bound of the reaction
        lowerBound - the lower bound of the reaction
        keff - the effective turnover rate of the synthetase of the reaction
        speciesIds - the list with the ids of all species in the reaction
        coefficients - the list with all species coefficients in the reaction, must have the same order as the list with species ids
        objectiveCoefficient - the coefficient of the flux objective of the reaction
        variableKind - can be either "continuous" or "discrete"
        subreactionMap - the map with the ids and coefficients of the subreactions that take part in the reaction, may be null
        synthetase - the id of the tRNA synthetase to charge the tRNA with an amino acid
        codon - the codon that is translated by the tRNA
        aminoAcid - the id of the amino acid that the tRNA transfers to a peptide
        Throws:
        org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException
        org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLValidationException

      • createPostTranslationReaction

        public void createPostTranslationReaction(org.sbml.jsbml.Model model,
                                          org.sbml.jsbml.ext.groups.GroupsModelPlugin groups,
                                          org.sbml.jsbml.ext.fbc.Objective objective,

                                          double objectiveCoefficient,
                                          java.lang.String variableKind,
                                          java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Double> subreactionMap,
                                          double aggregationPropensity,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.String> translocation,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.Double> multipliers,
                                          double propensityScaling,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.String> surfaceArea,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.Double> surfaceAreaValue,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.String> keqFolding,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.Double> keqValues,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.String> kFolding,
                                          java.util.List<java.lang.Double> kValues,
                                          java.lang.String biomassType,
                                          java.lang.String processed,
                                          java.lang.String unprocessed)
                                   throws org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException
        Create and add a post translation reaction to the model.

        The method adds the SBMLme attributes "dataID", "variableKind", "aggregationPropensity", "propensityScaling", "biomassType", "surfaceAreaInnerMembrane", "surfaceAreaOuterMembrane", "listOfSubreactionReferences" and "listOfTranslocationReferences" to the annotation of the reaction. The "listOfSubreactionReferences" contains all "subreactionReference" that take part in the reaction. The "listOfTranslocationReferences" contains all "translocationReferences" that take part in the reaction. The attributes "surfaceAreaInnerMembrane" and "surfaceAreaOuterMembrane" contain the value of the area occupied by the protein in the inner/outer membrane.

        Parameters:
        model - the SBML model
        groups - the GroupsModelPlugin of the SBML model
        objective - the active objective of the SBML model
        id - the id of the reaction to be added
        name - the name of the reaction, can be null
        dataId - the id of the process data object that is referred by the reaction in COBRAme, cannot be null or empty string
        upperBound - the upper bound of the reaction
        lowerBound - the lower bound of the reaction
        speciesIds - the list with the ids of all species in the reaction
        coefficients - the list with all species coefficients in the reaction, must have the same order as the list with species ids
        objectiveCoefficient - the coefficient of the flux objective of the reaction
        variableKind - can be either "continuous" or "discrete"
        subreactionMap - the map with the ids and coefficients of the subreactions that take part in the reaction, may be null
        aggregationPropensity - the aggregation propensity for the protein
        translocation - the list of ids of translocation pathways involved in the reaction, may be null
        multipliers - the list of multipliers belonging to the translocations, the order of both lists must be the same, may be null
        propensityScaling - accounts for the propensity of some peptides to be folded by certain chaperones
        surfaceArea - the list for the possible surfaces, valid values are "SA_inner_membrane" and "SA_outer_membrane", may be null
        surfaceAreaValue - the list for the area occupied by the protein in the surfaces given in the list "surfaceArea", the order of both lists must be the same, may be null
        keqFolding - list of temperatures for keq folding, may be null
        keqValues - list of temperature dependent keq folding values for the protein, may be null
        kFolding - list of temperatures for k folding, may be null
        kValues - list of temperature dependent rate constants for protein folding, may be null
        biomassType - the id of the biomass type added by the subreactions of the reaction, may be null
        processed - the id of the modified species
        unprocessed - the id of the species that is modified by the reaction
        Throws:
        org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException

      • createMetabolicReaction

        public void createMetabolicReaction(org.sbml.jsbml.Model model,
                                    org.sbml.jsbml.ext.groups.GroupsModelPlugin groups,
                                    org.sbml.jsbml.ext.fbc.Objective objective,
                                    java.lang.String id,
                                    java.lang.String name,
                                    java.lang.String dataId,
                                    double upperBound,
                                    double lowerBound,
                                    java.util.List<java.lang.String> speciesIds,
                                    java.util.List<java.lang.String> coefficients,
                                    double objectiveCoefficient,
                                    java.lang.String variableKind,
                                    double keff,
                                    boolean reverse,
                                    java.lang.String complexDataId)
                             throws org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException
        Create and add a metabolic reaction to the model.

        In COBRAme all reversible enzymatic reactions are broken into two irreversible reactions representing the two directions of the reaction. Therefore the boolean attribute "reverse" is added to the annotation of the reaction to define the direction. The attributes "dataId", "keff", "variableKind" and "complexDataId" are also added to the annotation.

        Parameters:
        model - the SBML model
        groups - the GroupsModelPlugin of the SBML model
        objective - the active objective of the SBML model
        id - the id of the reaction to be added
        name - the name of the reaction, can be null
        dataId - the id of the process data object that is referred by the reaction in COBRAme, cannot be null or empty string
        upperBound - the upper bound of the reaction
        lowerBound - the lower bound of the reaction
        keff - the effective turnover rate of the enzymes in the translocation pathway
        speciesIds - the list with the ids of all species in the reaction
        coefficients - the list with all species coefficients in the reaction, must have the same order as the list with species ids
        objectiveCoefficient - the coefficient of the flux objective of the reaction
        variableKind - can be either "continuous" or "discrete"
        keff - the effective turnover rate that couples enzymatic dilution to metabolic flux
        reverse - whether the reaction corresponds to the reverse reaction of the reversible reaction
        complexDataId - the id of the ComplexData object that details the enzyme which catalyzes the reaction
        Throws:
        org.sbml.jsbml.text.parser.ParseException
